               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770507-name-249" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-249" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-249" type="surname" value="CROOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-249" type="given" value="FANNY"></interp>FANNY CROOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of George Crook—in October, 1876, I was in the employ of Mr. Whiteley, of Westbourne Grove, and on that day Russell looked at some costumes, she selected one, price 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and gave her name Mrs. Reid, Hereford Square, Brompton—she banded me this cheque. (<hi rend="italic">This was on blank paper for</hi> 9<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., <hi rend="italic">payable to Mrs. A. Reid, or order, signed J. G. Reid, and dated 23rd October</hi>.) I asked her to put her name on the back, and she did so and asked for the change, which I gave her—the dress was sent to the address she gave and was returned three or four days afterwards.</p>
