                  </hi>. I am assistant to Messrs. Grant and Gask, silk mercers, of Oxford Street—on 9th December, Russell came and selected mantles to the amount of 31. Us. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—she gave her name Mrs. Murray, 19, Kildare Gardens, Bayswater, and handed me this cheque. (<hi rend="italic">For</hi> 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., <hi rend="italic">payable to Mrs. Murray, or order</hi>). She endorsed it "A. Murray" in my presence—the goods were sent the same day, and afterwards returned.</p>
