                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-259" type="surname" value="WRAPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-259" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN WRAPSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Messrs. Hitchcock and Co., silk mercers, of St. Paul's Church Yard—on 23rd March, Russell came and selected three mantles, value 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and she gave her name Mrs. Grenville, 90, Gloucester Place—she did not say which Gloucester Place—she gave me this cheque. (<hi rend="italic">This was on Glynn, Mills, and Co., for</hi> 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., <hi rend="italic">in favour of Mrs. Grenville, or order</hi>.) I asked her to endorse it and she did so—I took it to the cashier, and in consequence of what he told me she was given in custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770507-name-260" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-260" type="surname" value="WARNER"></interp>
